snippet.title: JOHNNY DEPP denies ABUSING AMBER HEARD - Hollywood TV
snippet.description:
Click to Subscribe! - http://bit.ly/SubHTV 
Hollywood TV is your source for daily celebrity news and gossip!
Johnny Depp denied Amber Heard’s abuse allegations and detailed his battle with drugs and alcohol in a London court on Tuesday. Depp is suing British tabloid The Sun for calling him a “wife beater.” Depp acknowledged heavy drinking and drug use, but said Ms. Heard’s claim that drugs and alcohol made him a “monster” was “delusional.” He testified that it was “inconceivable’’ that he would ever hit a woman, saying his Southern upbringing taught him it was “very important’’ to respect females.

Will Smith opened up about growing up in Philadelphia during an interview with Angela Rye.  "I've been called n----r by the cops in Philly on more than 10 occasions, right? I got stopped frequently. So, I understand what it's like, you know, to be in those circumstances with the police, to feel like you've been occupied. It's an occupying force."

Kendra Wilkinson has a new job. The former Girl Next Door who passed her real estate exam in June announced that she is joining The Agency, the company founded by Mauricio Umansky, husband  to Real Housewives of Beverly Hills star Kyle Richards.
